1
00:01:10,337 --> 00:01:12,738
By locking horns with Dhanraj
you have endangered your life.

2
00:01:19,847 --> 00:01:21,246
Scoundrel.

3
00:01:30,657 --> 00:01:33,820
"My dream girl,
when will you come?"

4
00:01:34,895 --> 00:01:36,556
Move. Move. Move.

5
00:01:36,663 --> 00:01:40,395
"My dream girl,
when will you come?"

6
00:01:40,501 --> 00:01:41,866
Wild people.

7
00:01:42,169 --> 00:01:43,568
You disturbed me
while | was singing.

8
00:01:48,175 --> 00:01:50,337
What's the matter?

9
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:52,276
Nothing.

10
00:01:52,513 --> 00:01:55,539
When | leave from home, my
wife helps me sit on the cycle.

11
00:01:55,649 --> 00:01:57,515
My man at the field
helps me get down.

12
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:59,313
| fell down. Who will help me?

13
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:01,513
| will help you.
- Why?

14
00:02:01,622 --> 00:02:03,681
Tell me. Why is everyone running?

15
00:02:11,899 --> 00:02:14,231
Hello, village head.
- Hello, village head.

16
00:02:14,501 --> 00:02:15,559
Hello, village head.

17
00:02:16,436 --> 00:02:17,494
Hello.

18
00:02:18,739 --> 00:02:22,801
Sir, everybody is
saying | Killed my wife.

19
00:02:23,177 --> 00:02:25,509
| swear on God. | didn't Kill her.

20
00:02:25,612 --> 00:02:26,909
| didn't Kill her.

21
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:33,882
Is there any
eye-witness of the murder?

22
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:36,615
Sir, | am the eye-witness.

23
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:40,487
Sir, husband and
wife were quarreling.

24
00:02:40,727 --> 00:02:42,252
He beat her very badly.

25
00:02:42,629 --> 00:02:44,222
Poor woman fell on
the ground in pain.

26
00:02:44,531 --> 00:02:45,555
| saw it.

27
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:49,596
Sir, | saw Rajpal taking
her to the north direction..

28
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:51,761
..and hanging her.

29
00:02:52,806 --> 00:02:55,605
No. Sir, it is a lie.

30
00:02:55,843 --> 00:02:56,901
It is a lie, sir.

31
00:02:58,445 --> 00:03:01,676
My lord, they are
concocting a story.

32
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:04,341
Is there no one to
challenge their lie?

33
00:03:04,451 --> 00:03:08,217
Rajpal, in a case
testimony is of utmost importance.

34
00:03:08,655 --> 00:03:10,555
There are two eye-witnesses.

35
00:03:10,824 --> 00:03:13,384
After committing murder when you
were fleeing, they caught you.

36
00:03:13,627 --> 00:03:15,356
It confirms our suspicion on you.

37
00:03:15,729 --> 00:03:17,595
The village council
finds you guilty..

38
00:03:17,764 --> 00:03:19,289
..and hands you over to the police.

39
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:23,967
Banwari, take Rajpal to
Rampura police station.

40
00:03:26,006 --> 00:03:29,203
This is the reward
for your service to me.

41
00:06:01,461 --> 00:06:04,795
After ruining a poor man's life,
they are feigning innocence. Look.

42
00:06:04,965 --> 00:06:06,399
They did such a derogatory deed.

43
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:08,696
And confidently gave false
testimony in the village council.

44
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:10,702
If Suraj had not come on time..

45
00:06:10,804 --> 00:06:13,102
..an innocent man
would have been hanged.

46
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:16,507
Fine. | don't say
whether they are guilty or not.

47
00:06:16,677 --> 00:06:18,873
But are you the village head?

48
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:20,879
Is there a council
to deliver justice?

49
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:22,005
Are there police?

50
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:23,776
Your son became a goon.

51
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:26,615
He barged into their
house and bashed them badly.

52
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,744
Is this justice?

53
00:06:27,855 --> 00:06:28,947
If they had suffered
serious injuries..

54
00:06:29,056 --> 00:06:30,114
..who would have been responsible?

55
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:32,787
If everyone does as they please..

56
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:33,985
..how will there be
peace in the village?

57
00:06:34,461 --> 00:06:35,860
What will happen if
everyone resorts to violence?

58
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:43,863
My son was wrong to barge into
their house and thrash them.

59
00:06:44,104 --> 00:06:45,435
Calling it a mistake is not enough.

60
00:06:45,539 --> 00:06:46,836
He will have to
apologize to everyone.

61
00:07:02,723 --> 00:07:06,159
| apologize for my son's mistake.

62
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:09,119
| will ensure that it
doesn't happen again.

63
00:07:10,731 --> 00:07:12,426
Hand both of them to the police.

64
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,592
Release Rajpal and bring him to me.

65
00:07:18,205 --> 00:07:19,468
Did you see, dear?

66
00:07:19,573 --> 00:07:20,870
What your brother is doing!

67
00:07:21,542 --> 00:07:25,206
In so many years | never
apologized to anyone in the village.

68
00:07:28,649 --> 00:07:30,208
Your brother is the new age don.

69
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:32,114
| used to always
think that negotiation..

70
00:07:32,219 --> 00:07:34,051
..bribery and
differentiation are enough.

71
00:07:35,556 --> 00:07:38,218
People say | always give sermon
to others but not to my family.

72
00:07:40,994 --> 00:07:42,826
Nobody can dare raise
his head in front of me.

73
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:48,196
If you interfere in
other people's affairs..

74
00:07:48,502 --> 00:07:49,628
..will we be able to
live in this village?

75
00:07:52,606 --> 00:07:55,098
If you knew the culprit,
why didn't you tell me?

76
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:56,734
Or else you should
have told the police.

77
00:08:08,155 --> 00:08:10,214
Tell me.

78
00:08:11,191 --> 00:08:13,523
Are you an incarnation
of God who has come..

79
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:15,522
..to liberate
sinners from their sins?

80
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:18,088
Sita.

81
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:20,758
Father is very angry. Bring a
glass of buttermilk. - Okay.

82
00:08:21,268 --> 00:08:23,498
Your father and | have
returned from the council.

83
00:08:23,604 --> 00:08:24,662
For me..

84
00:08:24,872 --> 00:08:26,897
What is this? You are
acting like a child.

85
00:08:28,075 --> 00:08:29,099
What is this?

86
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:31,804
You will have to take
permission to relieve yourself.

87
00:08:31,912 --> 00:08:34,244
| asked for a glass of buttermilk.

88
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:39,910
Father, buttermilk.

89
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,217
There is another policy
besides negotiation..

90
00:08:46,326 --> 00:08:47,885
..bribery and differentiation,
isn't there? - Penalty.

91
00:08:50,631 --> 00:08:51,689
Besides negotiation, bribery and..

92
00:08:51,765 --> 00:08:53,164
.differentiation there is
penalty too. You forgot.

93
00:08:54,268 --> 00:08:57,169
An innocent man is being
punished on false charges.

94
00:08:57,271 --> 00:08:59,069
You are telling me
to watch it silently.

95
00:08:59,339 --> 00:09:00,602
| follow penalty.

96
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,106
Righteousness woke up to
eradicate unrighteousness.

97
00:09:03,977 --> 00:09:05,536
You were telling me
to apologize. Why?

98
00:09:05,979 --> 00:09:07,777
Had your son not done this,
an innocent man..

99
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,815
..would have been punished.
Why should | apologize for that?

100
00:09:11,251 --> 00:09:13,686
If your son does a
good deed, praise him.

101
00:09:14,154 --> 00:09:15,280
Don't get angry needlessly.

102
00:09:16,256 --> 00:09:17,553
Who said | am wrong?

103
00:09:18,158 --> 00:09:20,252
People who give false testimony,
rape hapless women..

104
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,623
..and commit murder.

105
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:24,629
If | am defamed for
punishing such wicked people..

106
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:25,926
...| accept defamation.

107
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:29,736
If India's brave revolutionaries
had not shed blood..

108
00:09:29,837 --> 00:09:31,601
..we wouldn't have
called them martyrs.

109
00:09:32,272 --> 00:09:34,331
Why did you call me an
incarnation of God..

110
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:35,733
..who punishes sinners?

111
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:38,643
You must have noticed. When
mother cooks in the kitchen..

112
00:09:38,745 --> 00:09:39,871
..children help her a bit.

113
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:42,881
The same way God also
needs such kind of help.

114
00:09:45,786 --> 00:09:46,844
She is young. Forget it.

115
00:09:47,321 --> 00:09:50,586
Drink it. Father, let
anything happen in the village.

116
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:52,585
Why should we quarrel?
Drink buttermilk.

117
00:09:56,063 --> 00:09:58,088
Don't talk like a
naxalite in front of me.

118
00:09:58,999 --> 00:10:00,797
Your speeches won't
work in front of me.

119
00:10:01,135 --> 00:10:02,193
Do whatever you want.

120
00:10:02,636 --> 00:10:05,162
Can't you stop fighting
and live harmoniously?

121
00:10:05,873 --> 00:10:07,932
Dissection heals incurable wounds.

122
00:10:08,175 --> 00:10:10,667
Sweet talks can't heal it, father.

123
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:14,710
Suraj, what is your
goal in life? Tell me.

124
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:21,320
| have no goal or destination.

125
00:10:22,156 --> 00:10:24,386
Destinations are
formed automatically.

126
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:28,057
| can't live under the
burden of somebody's favor.

127
00:10:28,729 --> 00:10:30,993
It is difficult for a
culprit to escape from my grasp.

128
00:10:31,198 --> 00:10:34,190
Yes. Every youth talks like that.

129
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:36,729
It's rubbish.

130
00:10:37,037 --> 00:10:39,301
If you live here, you
will always quarrel.

131
00:10:39,406 --> 00:10:41,670
Go and live in Meerut.

132
00:10:42,042 --> 00:10:44,238
You know | didn't
come here willingly.

133
00:10:44,344 --> 00:10:46,176
You called me repeatedly.
That is why | came.

134
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,805
Now, you are telling me
to leave. So | am going.

135
00:10:47,915 --> 00:10:49,007
Brother.

136
00:10:49,283 --> 00:10:50,341
What is this?

137
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:52,919
You didn't come for five years
saying you are busy studying.

138
00:10:53,086 --> 00:10:55,680
You came recently and
you are returning so soon.

139
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:57,115
Don't stop me.

140
00:10:57,324 --> 00:10:59,053
My train will arrive at the station.

141
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,752
| will board the train.
And reach Meerut.

142
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:01,919
Got it?

143
00:11:02,362 --> 00:11:04,262
Take this, dear. Give it
at the workshop. - Okay.

144
00:11:09,403 --> 00:11:11,701
Suraj has come. He has come.

145
00:11:11,805 --> 00:11:14,035
Tonight, we will have a feast.

146
00:11:14,141 --> 00:11:17,839
He has come. He has come.
He has come.

147
00:11:18,078 --> 00:11:19,307
How is everyone?

148
00:11:19,813 --> 00:11:20,905
How are you, Paro?
- Fine.

149
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:22,175
Where is your father?
- He is there.

150
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:24,418
Is everything fine at home?

151
00:11:24,718 --> 00:11:26,345
The entire locality was
silent in your absence.

152
00:11:26,453 --> 00:11:27,978
Now, we will have fun.

153
00:11:28,489 --> 00:11:30,355
Come on. Let's have a party.

154
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:32,251
What is this?

155
00:11:32,493 --> 00:11:34,154
A bag. Remove it.

156
00:11:35,896 --> 00:11:37,295
Where are Bali and Ramu?

157
00:11:37,397 --> 00:11:40,765
Suraj, a lady came at
midnight to repair her car.

158
00:11:40,868 --> 00:11:42,393
We took pity on her
and fixed her car.

159
00:11:42,503 --> 00:11:43,868
She left without paying money.

160
00:11:43,971 --> 00:11:45,461
Both have gone to recover the money.

161
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:48,474
Did they misbehave with the lady?
- No.

162
00:11:48,909 --> 00:11:50,240
How did she leave
without paying money?

163
00:11:50,344 --> 00:11:51,812
She was a strange lady.

164
00:11:55,949 --> 00:11:57,041
Suraj.
- Suraj.

165
00:11:57,151 --> 00:11:58,880
When did you come?
- What happened to you?

166
00:11:58,986 --> 00:12:00,249
It's the game of destiny.

167
00:12:00,354 --> 00:12:02,880
We went to recover
money from that lady.

168
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:04,958
We went there. She
had big Alsatian dogs.

169
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:06,958
They came running to hug us.

170
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,084
They clawed us.

171
00:12:08,195 --> 00:12:09,253
That lady didn't stop them?

172
00:12:10,831 --> 00:12:12,458
No. She told them to attack us.

173
00:12:12,766 --> 00:12:14,256
If she had only attacked us,
we would have understood.

174
00:12:14,368 --> 00:12:15,802
But she was standing
in her balcony proudly..

175
00:12:15,903 --> 00:12:17,132
..and combing her hair.

176
00:12:17,237 --> 00:12:18,329
And she said,
"Don't let them escape.”

177
00:12:18,438 --> 00:12:19,735
She made the dogs run after us.

178
00:12:19,973 --> 00:12:22,305
Who is that lady
who didn't pay money?

179
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:23,899
Her name is Veena.

180
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:25,445
She studies in G.V Lady college.

181
00:12:25,512 --> 00:12:29,346
Her car number is TMS 6006.

182
00:12:36,924 --> 00:12:38,050
Hi.
- Hi.

183
00:12:47,534 --> 00:12:49,832
Good morning. - Who are you?
Why are you sitting in the car?

184
00:12:49,937 --> 00:12:52,099
| am a mechanic. | am
taking the car to the workshop.

185
00:12:52,206 --> 00:12:54,174
Madam had told me. Give this to her.

186
00:12:54,842 --> 00:12:56,810
Your name?
- Paratha.

187
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,036
Paratha?
-Yes.

188
00:12:59,046 --> 00:13:01,447
| gave the correct address.
She will surely come.

189
00:13:09,957 --> 00:13:11,789
Four girls are coming in a cab.

190
00:13:15,162 --> 00:13:17,563
Mister. Mister.

191
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,191
This is my car.

192
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:26,830
Beautiful.
- What?

193
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:28,237
| said it's a beautiful car.

194
00:13:28,342 --> 00:13:29,468
Why did you bring my car here?

195
00:13:29,576 --> 00:13:31,908
For repairing.
- Who said my car has broken down?

196
00:13:32,012 --> 00:13:34,106
You didn't pay money for
reparation. So | brought it here.

197
00:13:34,214 --> 00:13:35,238
Whom are you threatening?

198
00:13:35,349 --> 00:13:37,408
Look, mister. | will tell the
police to put you in the lockup.

199
00:13:37,484 --> 00:13:39,384
Got it?
- Great! What times are these!

200
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:41,318
The guilty rebukes the innocent.

201
00:13:41,421 --> 00:13:42,445
Look there. Look there.

202
00:13:46,126 --> 00:13:48,151
Look. See their plight.

203
00:13:49,129 --> 00:13:50,153
They will bite me.

204
00:13:55,602 --> 00:13:56,899
What happened to them?

205
00:13:58,906 --> 00:14:01,034
They are dear to me.
Very dear to me.

206
00:14:01,141 --> 00:14:02,302
My friends since the past 20 years.

207
00:14:07,047 --> 00:14:09,141
They have been living with
me for the past 25 years.

208
00:14:09,483 --> 00:14:11,451
The doctor gave them 56 injections.

209
00:14:11,652 --> 00:14:12,949
Their survival seems unlikely.

210
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:15,486
Their survival
really seems unlikely?

211
00:14:15,556 --> 00:14:18,582
Really. These innocent boys
will die within four to five days.

212
00:14:18,892 --> 00:14:19,950
And you will be put behind bars.

213
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,495
Should | pity them
or should | pity you?

214
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:25,594
Veena, listen to me.
- What happened?

215
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:27,367
He is giving threat of
the police. Shall we leave?

216
00:14:27,668 --> 00:14:29,602
Staying here is
like inviting trouble.

217
00:14:31,572 --> 00:14:33,040
| don't know what
will happen. Let's go.

218
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,403
Wait. | will handle everything.

219
00:14:37,144 --> 00:14:38,509
What trouble is this?

220
00:14:38,612 --> 00:14:40,341
| didn't unleash my
dogs on them deliberately.

221
00:14:40,447 --> 00:14:43,212
Unknowingly the
dogs got angry. And..

222
00:14:48,055 --> 00:14:49,545
They are the apple of my eyes.

223
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:51,583
They are very precious.

224
00:14:52,459 --> 00:14:55,019
Take this. A pearl ring.
- It's real?

225
00:14:55,229 --> 00:14:56,663
It's worth Rs.7000.

226
00:14:57,431 --> 00:14:59,160
Give me the car.

227
00:14:59,266 --> 00:15:00,290
Take it.

228
00:15:04,605 --> 00:15:06,039
Good evening, ma'am.
- Good evening.

229
00:15:08,308 --> 00:15:09,400
Really.

230
00:15:11,979 --> 00:15:13,208
She has come.

231
00:15:13,313 --> 00:15:14,508
She has come.

232
00:15:14,615 --> 00:15:15,673
She has come.

233
00:15:16,316 --> 00:15:18,580
Hello.
- Hello.

234
00:15:21,555 --> 00:15:24,024
How did he come here?
- Is something fishy?

235
00:15:24,124 --> 00:15:25,523
| also think so.

236
00:15:27,361 --> 00:15:28,692
Excuse me.
- Yes, please.

237
00:15:29,196 --> 00:15:30,664
I am Vishnu.
- So what?

238
00:15:31,231 --> 00:15:33,427
Pleased to meet you.
-1 am not pleased.

239
00:16:08,435 --> 00:16:10,529
Shut up. Why have you come here?
To create a scene?

240
00:16:10,637 --> 00:16:11,729
Get up.

241
00:16:12,239 --> 00:16:13,673
What scene?

242
00:16:13,774 --> 00:16:15,333
Who let them in?

243
00:16:16,743 --> 00:16:18,006
Manager.

244
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,406
Manager.

245
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:25,982
It was silly of us to
call you here. - Shut up.

246
00:16:26,086 --> 00:16:28,521
Why? | will beat you with
my slippers. Understood?

247
00:16:29,356 --> 00:16:31,757
Don't get angry.
- Look at this.

248
00:16:32,059 --> 00:16:33,288
What is this?

249
00:16:33,393 --> 00:16:34,656
Ma'am, you see..
- What you see?

250
00:16:34,761 --> 00:16:36,251
Why did you allow them in
when they are not wearing suits?

251
00:16:36,363 --> 00:16:37,990
I am sorry, ma'am.
- Nothing doing.

252
00:16:38,098 --> 00:16:40,328
Throw these beggars
out within five minutes.

253
00:16:40,434 --> 00:16:42,198
Otherwise you will be dismissed.
Understand?

254
00:16:42,269 --> 00:16:44,135
Yes, ma'am.
