01:00:51,285 --> 01:00:55,085
.1 will be the
permanent owner of this place.

778
01:00:57,291 --> 01:00:58,725
There is a person in that village.

779
01:00:58,826 --> 01:01:00,316
A spy. Yes.
- Call him.

780
01:01:00,861 --> 01:01:02,329
Start the work today itself.

781
01:01:24,918 --> 01:01:25,976
Father.

782
01:01:27,988 --> 01:01:29,012
Father.

783
01:01:33,160 --> 01:01:34,218
Father.

784
01:01:36,396 --> 01:01:38,831
Brother. Brother.

785
01:01:46,006 --> 01:01:47,064
Brother.

786
01:01:53,380 --> 01:01:59,877
He died saying you will surely come.

787
01:02:08,228 --> 01:02:10,026
Sir, hello.
- Hello. Hello.

788
01:02:10,130 --> 01:02:12,064
He.. He is one of the
candidates contesting for the post..

789
01:02:12,499 --> 01:02:16,265
..of the village head
after Jai Prakash's death.

790
01:02:16,537 --> 01:02:18,403
Doesn't he have a
strong personality?

791
01:02:18,505 --> 01:02:20,269
My name is Banwari. Hello.

792
01:02:21,275 --> 01:02:22,868
Banwari. Look.

793
01:02:23,410 --> 01:02:26,436
Since generations
Jai Prakash's family..

794
01:02:26,847 --> 01:02:28,178
..and my family have been enemies.

795
01:02:28,883 --> 01:02:33,150
After his death we should
forget this quarrel and unite.

796
01:02:33,387 --> 01:02:35,321
Khata told me everything.
- Okay.

797
01:02:35,422 --> 01:02:36,856
But | have a request.
-Yes.

798
01:02:36,957 --> 01:02:40,860
You will have to make
someone the head of Rajoli village.

799
01:02:41,061 --> 01:02:42,859
| will make you the village head.

800
01:02:43,964 --> 01:02:47,332
But here..
- 1 will do your bidding.

801
01:02:47,501 --> 01:02:49,401
Everybody will imitate you.

802
01:02:49,703 --> 01:02:52,798
You fool. Why did you sneeze?

803
01:02:53,440 --> 01:02:54,498
Put your thumbprint.

804
01:02:57,912 --> 01:02:59,971
Why are you putting your
thumbprint on a blank paper?

805
01:03:00,180 --> 01:03:02,478
We are mortgaging
our lands to Dhanraj.

806
01:03:03,517 --> 01:03:05,383
Did you give them money?

807
01:03:07,187 --> 01:03:08,780
| have a tender heart.

808
01:03:09,056 --> 01:03:12,321
| couldn't see the
villagers' woes. So | helped them.

809
01:03:12,426 --> 01:03:14,087
Why did you have to sell
your flourishing fields..

810
01:03:14,194 --> 01:03:15,423
..and leave the village?

811
01:03:15,529 --> 01:03:18,157
Earlier your father used to lend
money without charging interest.

812
01:03:18,265 --> 01:03:20,393
He would even give
us manure for free.

813
01:03:20,501 --> 01:03:23,937
But when you went to prison,
his heart broke.

814
01:03:24,037 --> 01:03:25,129
He would only lie on the bed.

815
01:03:26,240 --> 01:03:29,141
Banwari, this is how
you have helped them.

816
01:03:29,944 --> 01:03:32,003
As a proof that our
villagers are honest..

817
01:03:32,112 --> 01:03:34,240
..and to recover
the borrowed money..

818
01:03:34,348 --> 01:03:37,079
..I have made this arrangement.

819
01:03:38,152 --> 01:03:40,519
Why didn't you help them get a
loan from the government committee?

820
01:03:41,455 --> 01:03:45,824
There are many such
committees in the village.

821
01:03:46,026 --> 01:03:48,586
Not just that. Dhanraj has
a good influence over them.

822
01:03:48,996 --> 01:03:51,363
But why did he lend
money to our villagers?

823
01:03:52,099 --> 01:03:56,093
To seize our small farms.

824
01:03:56,203 --> 01:04:00,162
And later, he wishes to
control the entire village.

825
01:04:00,908 --> 01:04:02,501
What is the total amount?

826
01:04:02,576 --> 01:04:03,839
It's a large sum.

827
01:04:03,944 --> 01:04:06,436
Look, manager. Repay the loan
that our villagers have taken.

828
01:04:06,547 --> 01:04:07,605
The money..

829
01:04:08,182 --> 01:04:11,482
Nobody from our village
will sign these papers.

830
01:04:12,519 --> 01:04:13,577
Khata.

831
01:04:14,221 --> 01:04:15,313
Khata, come.

832
01:04:15,556 --> 01:04:17,854
What is this? - Shall we
take the other signatures?

833
01:04:23,530 --> 01:04:25,055
Where did Kalu, Moti, Ramu..

834
01:04:25,165 --> 01:04:26,462
..all those who work
in our village go?

835
01:04:26,967 --> 01:04:29,993
They had taken a loan from Dhanraj.

836
01:04:30,437 --> 01:04:32,371
They couldn't repay the loan.

837
01:04:32,473 --> 01:04:35,499
So they are working for Dhanraj.

838
01:04:36,510 --> 01:04:37,875
As slaves?
-Yes.

839
01:04:38,078 --> 01:04:42,015
Come on. Work quickly. Why
are you staring at my face?

840
01:04:45,352 --> 01:04:46,410
Look, Suraj is coming.

841
01:04:46,520 --> 01:04:48,147
Suraj? Why is he coming here?

842
01:04:50,257 --> 01:04:51,281
Hello.
- Hello.

843
01:04:52,226 --> 01:04:53,660
My villagers, come here.

844
01:04:53,961 --> 01:04:55,053
Why did you come? Why did you come?

845
01:04:55,162 --> 01:04:56,288
Why are you calling them?

846
01:04:56,697 --> 01:04:59,428
| will buy them and
sell them to your master.

847
01:04:59,667 --> 01:05:01,032
Are you joking?

848
01:05:02,703 --> 01:05:03,932
Rs.10000.

849
01:05:04,171 --> 01:05:05,229
Make the receipt.

850
01:07:42,262 --> 01:07:43,821
Come on, everyone.
- Come on. Come on.

851
01:07:50,237 --> 01:07:52,228
Suraj has come. Suraj has come.

852
01:07:53,173 --> 01:07:54,231
Look.

853
01:07:54,475 --> 01:07:58,275
Henceforth all workers from my
village will work in my farms.

854
01:07:58,379 --> 01:07:59,403
Not as unpaid workers.

855
01:07:59,647 --> 01:08:00,773
Everybody will work together.

856
01:08:01,315 --> 01:08:03,841
The profit will be equally
divided amongst everyone.

857
01:08:04,385 --> 01:08:05,682
| will have a share.

858
01:08:06,220 --> 01:08:08,382
Long live Suraj Prakash,
the new age don!

859
01:08:08,455 --> 01:08:10,549
Long live Suraj Prakash,
the don of our village!

860
01:08:10,657 --> 01:08:12,853
Long live Suraj Prakash,
the don of our village!

861
01:08:13,160 --> 01:08:15,322
Long live Suraj Prakash,
the don of our village!

862
01:08:15,429 --> 01:08:17,158
Long live Suraj Prakash,
the don of our village!

863
01:08:17,264 --> 01:08:19,358
Stop. - Long live Suraj Prakash,
the don of poor people! - Stop.

864
01:08:20,734 --> 01:08:24,102
You spend half your life
shouting slogans for others.

865
01:08:24,605 --> 01:08:25,766
What did those
people who became rich..

866
01:08:25,873 --> 01:08:27,170
..because of you do for you?

867
01:08:27,474 --> 01:08:28,805
They sold their motherland.

868
01:08:29,376 --> 01:08:30,775
And became homeless.

869
01:08:31,512 --> 01:08:32,877
You worship your motherland.

870
01:08:33,180 --> 01:08:34,841
You don't need to work for anyone.

871
01:08:35,482 --> 01:08:36,813
One man gives a lecture.

872
01:08:37,384 --> 01:08:39,284
And lakhs of people listen to him.

873
01:08:39,386 --> 01:08:40,547
That era is gone.

874
01:08:40,888 --> 01:08:43,482
Lakhs of people
should toil together.

875
01:08:43,791 --> 01:08:46,419
The day someone comes to guide
them and value their worth..

876
01:08:46,527 --> 01:08:49,827
..that day our country will prosper.

877
01:08:50,397 --> 01:08:54,595
Henceforth | don't want to
hear slogans in this village.

878
01:08:55,636 --> 01:08:58,367
He brainwashed them
and became their leader.

879
01:08:58,472 --> 01:09:00,270
He doesn't even
want to hear slogans.

880
01:09:00,374 --> 01:09:03,241
He is luring
people with sweet talks.

881
01:09:03,344 --> 01:09:05,210
He talks about our wellbeing.

882
01:09:05,312 --> 01:09:06,473
Shut up.
-Yes.

883
01:09:06,580 --> 01:09:07,638
Will you spoil my
eardrums by yelling?

884
01:09:07,748 --> 01:09:08,909
Put cotton in your ears.

885
01:09:09,216 --> 01:09:11,514
Take this.
- Rummy show.

886
01:09:11,619 --> 01:09:15,146
Oh, no. What is this?
He always wins.

887
01:09:15,355 --> 01:09:16,584
Why do we play?

888
01:09:16,890 --> 01:09:18,324
We should give him
money without playing.

889
01:09:18,559 --> 01:09:20,220
Don't play.

890
01:09:20,794 --> 01:09:22,523
Come on.
- Brother has come.

891
01:09:23,564 --> 01:09:24,656
Listen, village head.
-Yes.

892
01:09:24,932 --> 01:09:27,401
| need your cronies' help.

893
01:09:27,835 --> 01:09:30,395
What do you want to do?
Tell me. We will do it.

894
01:09:30,704 --> 01:09:32,502
We don't want a share.
- We want wages.

895
01:09:32,606 --> 01:09:34,700
We don't want a share.
- We want wages.

896
01:09:34,808 --> 01:09:36,902
For our hard work.
- We want wages.

897
01:09:37,211 --> 01:09:39,305
For our hard work.
- We want wages.

898
01:09:39,380 --> 01:09:42,645
For their every atrocity.
- We have an answer.

899
01:09:42,750 --> 01:09:46,448
For their every atrocity.
- We have an answer.

900
01:09:46,887 --> 01:09:49,356
| had not imagined all
of you will demand this.

901
01:09:49,757 --> 01:09:51,418
Is there anything lacking? Tell me.

902
01:09:51,525 --> 01:09:52,959
1 will try to fulfill it.

903
01:09:53,460 --> 01:09:56,555
Why are you talking to us?
Talk to our leader.

904
01:09:56,664 --> 01:09:57,688
Surely.

905
01:09:57,965 --> 01:10:00,332
This is the rule.
Who is your leader?

906
01:10:01,235 --> 01:10:03,897
Chaudhary Shankarlal.
- Chaudhary Shankarlal.

907
01:10:05,306 --> 01:10:08,833
We will surely take it.
- Our right.

908
01:10:09,343 --> 01:10:10,401
Come.

909
01:10:11,245 --> 01:10:12,303
Sit.

910
01:10:12,813 --> 01:10:15,805
| am the leader.
Chaudhary Shankarlal.

911
01:10:16,283 --> 01:10:17,773
You are the contractor.

912
01:10:17,885 --> 01:10:18,977
You are the accountant.

913
01:10:19,586 --> 01:10:24,422
When you quarrel, you
remember the village head.

914
01:10:24,959 --> 01:10:27,724
No. My father was looking
after the farms since a long time.

915
01:10:27,828 --> 01:10:29,660
Now, | look after it.
- Since the time you have come..

916
01:10:29,763 --> 01:10:30,787
.. the workers have got spoilt.

917
01:10:31,465 --> 01:10:33,433
Did it happen because of me?

918
01:10:33,801 --> 01:10:34,859
Of course.

919
01:10:35,035 --> 01:10:38,733
Why did you call the
workers from other villagers?

920
01:10:39,006 --> 01:10:40,496
| thought they would like ..

921
01:10:40,608 --> 01:10:41,632
.. to lead a comfortable
life in their village.

922
01:10:41,742 --> 01:10:43,574
Who are you to decide this?

923
01:10:44,345 --> 01:10:46,245
Nobody else took the initiative.
So | took it.

924
01:10:46,513 --> 01:10:47,571
What did | do wrong?

925
01:10:47,681 --> 01:10:50,582
Small farmers had taken
a loan from Mr. Dhanraj.

926
01:10:50,818 --> 01:10:52,752
There had made an agreement.

927
01:10:52,853 --> 01:10:54,582
Who are you to cancel it?

928
01:10:54,855 --> 01:10:57,722
It is my habit to fight
injustice and to stop it.

929
01:10:58,392 --> 01:10:59,416
Oh ho.

930
01:10:59,860 --> 01:11:01,794
You will take law in your hands.

931
01:11:01,895 --> 01:11:05,297
What if they can't repay the loan?

932
01:11:05,466 --> 01:11:07,628
You will take law in your hand.

933
01:11:07,735 --> 01:11:09,225
Isn't this your plan?

934
01:11:15,910 --> 01:11:17,674
| have understood your plan.

935
01:11:17,778 --> 01:11:19,405
| see. So you have understood.

936
01:11:19,513 --> 01:11:20,912
How did it begin?

937
01:11:21,615 --> 01:11:23,549
Is this quarrel against me or them?

938
01:11:23,884 --> 01:11:26,819
Yes. We will have to pay
the workers double wages.

939
01:11:26,921 --> 01:11:29,015
And two days off in a week.

940
01:11:29,390 --> 01:11:31,290
How will they feed
themselves for two days?

941
01:11:31,392 --> 01:11:33,417
Don't worry about that.

942
01:11:36,497 --> 01:11:39,865
Since generations my workers
have been working in your farms.

943
01:11:40,367 --> 01:11:43,826
You will have to transfer
the farms in their names.

944
01:11:44,038 --> 01:11:47,406
Why? Dhanraj will take mortgaged
farms by giving them a loan?

945
01:11:47,608 --> 01:11:49,770
Don't argue with me.

946
01:11:50,077 --> 01:11:51,340
Do as | say.

947
01:11:51,679 --> 01:11:54,808
Don't interfere when the
farms will be transferred..

948
01:11:56,350 --> 01:11:58,284
..in Mr. Dhanraj's name.

949
01:11:58,652 --> 01:12:01,349
If you want, you can
take your money back.

950
01:12:01,455 --> 01:12:02,752
What if | don't want that?

951
01:12:02,857 --> 01:12:07,727
What else? The quarrel will
intensify. Blood will be shed.

952
01:12:08,362 --> 01:12:09,830
And then wails.

953
01:12:10,631 --> 01:12:12,793
Today, | came to
meet you respectfully.

954
01:12:13,567 --> 01:12:16,298
But now, | accept your challenge.

955
01:12:16,937 --> 01:12:19,599
| won't let the workers
get trapped in your ruse.

956
01:12:19,807 --> 01:12:21,639
Is it a challenge?
- Yes. It's a challenge.

957
01:12:21,842 --> 01:12:22,900
See you.

958
01:12:26,046 --> 01:12:27,536
Suraj, what is this?

959
01:12:27,648 --> 01:12:29,343
You went to the village.
And never returned.

960
01:12:29,650 --> 01:12:31,015
| have settled down in
the village permanently.

961
01:12:31,118 --> 01:12:33,985
Look, bring all unemployed
students who study with us.

962
01:12:34,088 --> 01:12:36,682
| want to talk to them. Later,
you will also have to come with me.

963
01:12:36,857 --> 01:12:40,919
What is this? How will |
find all unemployed students?

964
01:12:45,065 --> 01:12:48,091
Why did all of you come here?
To lock horns with me?

965
01:12:48,736 --> 01:12:52,001
No. When educated
city-bred are toiling..

966
01:12:52,106 --> 01:12:53,733
..should we sit at home?

967
01:13:01,615 --> 01:13:02,639
Madhavi, what is the matter?

968
01:13:02,750 --> 01:13:04,844
Nowadays your sister is
not to be seen at night.

969
01:13:05,019 --> 01:13:07,681
Where is she?
- Why are you asking me repeatedly?

970
01:13:08,022 --> 01:13:11,014
Because | don't want
her to fall for a goon.

971
01:13:11,459 --> 01:13:12,517
If you are so concerned about her..

972
01:13:12,626 --> 01:13:15,425
..why don't you find a
decent boy and get her married?

973
01:13:15,629 --> 01:13:17,757
Who will conduct his son's
marriage into your family?

974
01:13:17,865 --> 01:13:18,923
Do one thing.

975
01:13:19,133 --> 01:13:21,500
| have kept you as my mistress.

976
01:13:21,568 --> 01:13:23,832
| will gladly keep your
sister as my mistress.

977
01:13:25,539 --> 01:13:27,598
It's a sin to be born as a woman.

978
01:13:27,941 --> 01:13:29,636
On top of that a ‘Devdasi"
{A woman married to a deity).

979
01:13:31,011 --> 01:13:34,470
Destiny.
- Slowly. Slowly. Slowly.

980
01:13:43,190 --> 01:13:46,922
This terrifying place is
very eerie. Let's leave.

981
01:13:47,728 --> 01:13:48,786
Why? What is here?

982
01:13:49,063 --> 01:13:52,966
Nothing. Ghosts and spirits
haunt this place at night.

983
01:13:54,568 --> 01:13:55,967
| love ghosts and spirits.

984
01:13:56,770 --> 01:13:58,431
If they come, | will talk to them.

985
01:13:58,706 --> 01:14:01,641
You can go.
- You will talk to ghosts? How?

986
01:14:02,443 --> 01:14:05,413
| spoke to you. Is it
difficult to talk to ghosts?

987
01:14:05,713 --> 01:14:07,181
My wife also says the same thing.

988
01:14:07,481 --> 01:14:09,882
| was saying because..
- | said leave.

989
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:34,058
Why are you wandering here?

990
01:15:36,237 --> 01:15:38,001
Why are you afraid?

991
01:15:40,608 --> 01:15:42,167
| wished her well.

992
01:15:42,743 --> 01:15:44,939
And she is driving me
crazy with her wails.

993
01:15:46,280 --> 01:15:47,805
You are Dholakia Baldeva,
aren't you?

994
01:15:47,915 --> 01:15:51,874
I was. Now, I am Madhavi's uncle.

995
01:15:52,053 --> 01:15:53,680
She is my sister's daughter.

996
01:15:54,054 --> 01:15:55,920
Who is Madhavi?

997
01:15:56,023 --> 01:16:00,085
Madhavi is the ‘Devdasi'
who danced in our temple.

998
01:16:00,294 --> 01:16:01,693
She is her younger sister.

999
01:16:01,829 --> 01:16:03,058
Her name is Vidya.

1000
01:16:03,264 --> 01:16:04,959
Why is she wandering alone at night?

1001
01:16:05,066 --> 01:16:06,534
She has lost her sense.

1002
01:16:06,700 --> 01:16:09,795
Landlord Sevaklal wants
to give her a grand car..

1003
01:16:09,904 --> 01:16:12,635
..and a bungalow
surrounded by a garden.

1004
01:16:12,873 --> 01:16:16,138
But she is crying inconsolably.

1005
01:16:16,677 --> 01:16:18,839
We are low-caste people.

1006
01:16:19,079 --> 01:16:21,138
How can we lead a
dignified life? Tell me.

1007
01:16:22,683 --> 01:16:24,777
You beat me. Why do beat me?

1008
01:16:25,085 --> 01:16:29,921
Get in. - Open. Open.
Open. Open the door. Open.

1009
01:16:32,659 --> 01:16:34,024
Where are you going quietly?

1010
01:16:35,229 --> 01:16:36,287
Come to my house.

1011
01:16:38,132 --> 01:16:39,759
You are afraid because | am drunk?

1012
01:16:42,236 --> 01:16:44,068
Don't be afraid. Come.

1013
01:17:05,693 --> 01:17:08,060
Sita. Sit here.

1014
01:17:08,162 --> 01:17:10,756
No. Wait. Sita.

1015
01:17:12,633 --> 01:17:13,657
Sita.

1016
01:17:16,704 --> 01:17:18,832
It is you? How did you come here?

1017
01:17:18,939 --> 01:17:19,997
Did you come to meet brother?

1018
01:17:20,741 --> 01:17:23,233
| saw your dance.
You dance very well.

1019
01:17:23,377 --> 01:17:24,606
He is my brother.

1020
01:17:24,912 --> 01:17:25,970
Hello.

1021
01:17:26,080 --> 01:17:27,912
Brother, she is a great dancer.

1022
01:17:28,015 --> 01:17:29,073
Her name is Vidya.

1023
01:17:29,683 --> 01:17:30,741
Is that so?

1024
01:17:32,920 --> 01:17:35,082
No, brother. | have
told you so many times.

1025
01:17:35,189 --> 01:17:36,247
Don't drink.

1026
01:17:36,357 --> 01:17:38,223
Don't scold. Don't scold.

1027
01:17:38,692 --> 01:17:39,955
Listen to me.

1028
01:17:40,160 --> 01:17:44,961
She is an orphan girl.
She will stay here.

1029
01:17:45,666 --> 01:17:47,156
You don't mind, do you?

1030
01:17:47,368 --> 01:17:49,268
Why will you mind?

1031
01:17:55,809 --> 01:17:56,833
Don't worry.

1032
01:17:56,944 --> 01:17:59,345
God is there. Stay here.

1033
01:17:59,446 --> 01:18:01,881
He will handle everything.

1034
01:18:07,788 --> 01:18:08,846
Stop.

1035
01:18:10,724 --> 01:18:12,419
Stop. Come here. Come here.

1036
01:18:13,360 --> 01:18:17,194
| was waiting for your return.

1037
01:18:17,798 --> 01:18:20,790
Once you live in a bungalow,
you will forget your old lover.

1038
01:18:21,102 --> 01:18:22,900
Come. Come with me quietly.

1039
01:18:23,103 --> 01:18:24,161
Otherwise..

1040
01:18:24,371 --> 01:18:25,395
| will hand you over to the police.

1041
01:18:25,706 --> 01:18:26,764
Who is it?

1042
01:18:28,376 --> 01:18:30,208
You are amazing!

1043
01:18:30,377 --> 01:18:33,244
You dare to threaten
a girl in my village?

1044
01:18:33,347 --> 01:18:37,841
Landlord Sevaklal said
he will pay me Rs.10000.

1045
01:18:38,185 --> 01:18:40,415
You brought her along with
you without paying money.

1046
01:18:40,721 --> 01:18:41,779
Is it fair?

1047
01:18:44,224 --> 01:18:45,248
Get lost.

1048
01:18:48,395 --> 01:18:49,829
If you want to feed yourself, toil.

1049
01:18:50,131 --> 01:18:51,929
Don't sell helpless people and
earn money by dishonest means.

1050
01:18:52,433 --> 01:18:55,266
If you come here again,
| won't spare you.

1051
01:18:56,804 --> 01:18:58,101
Are the servants dead?

1052
01:18:58,239 --> 01:18:59,434
Why did you venture out
of the house? Come on.

1053
01:19:06,914 --> 01:19:07,972
What nonsense is he talking?

1054
01:19:09,116 --> 01:19:10,277
Educated people have come.

1055
01:19:10,418 --> 01:19:12,409
Should we become cowards?
- No.

1056
01:19:12,953 --> 01:19:14,819
| don't know what
spell Suraj has cast.

1057
01:19:14,922 --> 01:19:17,914
All women in the
village say he is good.

1058
01:19:18,025 --> 01:19:21,154
Every woman likes Suraj a lot.

1059
01:19:21,495 --> 01:19:23,020
Village head.
-Yes.

1060
01:19:23,130 --> 01:19:24,291
| don't know what
solution you have thought..

1061
01:19:24,398 --> 01:19:25,456
..and what you will do.

1062
01:19:25,933 --> 01:19:28,300
Drive away the
educated boys immediately.

1063
01:21:40,534 --> 01:21:42,195
Come on. Come on. Run quickly.

1064
01:21:42,302 --> 01:21:44,066
Hurry up.

1065
01:21:47,441 --> 01:21:48,533
They ran away. They ran away.

1066
01:21:48,642 --> 01:21:50,201
They ran away. They
ran away. They ran away.

1067
01:21:50,544 --> 01:21:52,410
They ran away. They
ran away. They ran away.

1068
01:21:52,513 --> 01:21:54,379
They ran away. They
ran away. They ran away.

1069
01:21:54,481 --> 01:21:58,145
Eunuch, you cling to me. Stay away.

1070
01:21:59,286 --> 01:22:00,344
They ran away.

1071
01:22:07,294 --> 01:22:10,559
Is she your wife?
- My wife died two years ago.

1072
01:22:10,965 --> 01:22:12,194
Do the villagers know?

1073
01:22:12,566 --> 01:22:14,933
Is this something to
shout from the rooftop?

1074
01:22:15,569 --> 01:22:17,162
If it becomes common knowledge..

1075
01:22:17,271 --> 01:22:19,239
..my image will be tarnished.

1076
01:22:19,506 --> 01:22:22,407
If you swear not to tell
anyone about our plan.. - Yes.

1077
01:22:22,509 --> 01:22:24,500
It will always remain a secret.
- Okay.

1078
01:22:24,578 --> 01:22:25,943
Understood?
-Yes.

1079
01:22:26,047 --> 01:22:27,105
Or not?

1080
01:22:29,383 --> 01:22:31,511
Come. Come. When did you come?

1081
01:22:31,952 --> 01:22:33,113
Just now.

1082
01:22:33,420 --> 01:22:34,979
Village head, sit there.

1083
01:22:35,089 --> 01:22:37,319
He said this chair is yours.

1084
01:22:37,525 --> 01:22:39,425
Bring another chair.
- Right away.

1085
01:22:40,694 --> 01:22:44,961
What happened? - Last night
| had a fight with a bull.

1086
01:22:45,232 --> 01:22:46,290
Did it beat you badly?

1087
01:22:46,467 --> 01:22:47,696
Beware of bulls.

1088
01:22:48,402 --> 01:22:51,235
| was careful. But
it got infuriated.

1089
01:22:51,439 --> 01:22:53,032
Sit.
- Okay.

1090
01:22:53,140 --> 01:22:54,198
Where will you hide your hand?

1091
01:22:54,575 --> 01:22:56,669
That's why | was at home.

1092
01:22:57,478 --> 01:23:00,209
How much money did Dhanraj
give you for this unfair strike?

1093
01:23:00,281 --> 01:23:02,511
At present he has
given me only Rs.15000.

1094
01:23:02,616 --> 01:23:04,209
He will pay me more.

1095
01:23:04,585 --> 01:23:06,144
If | want to end the
strike immediately..

1096
01:23:06,220 --> 01:23:07,278
..what will | have to give you?

1097
01:23:07,354 --> 01:23:09,254
Whatever you wish.

1098
01:23:11,092 --> 01:23:12,491
| will have to give something?
-Yes.

1099
01:23:13,527 --> 01:23:15,723
It's not compulsory.

1100
01:23:16,030 --> 01:23:18,226
Give whatever you want.
Otherwise forget it.

1101
01:23:19,200 --> 01:23:20,565
Village head.
-Yes.

1102
01:23:21,335 --> 01:23:24,134
If | give money,
will you end the strike?

1103
01:23:26,040 --> 01:23:28,168
That's why | have
started the strike.

1104
01:23:29,276 --> 01:23:31,711
Don't you feel you
are betraying him?

1105
01:23:32,313 --> 01:23:34,441
What is this?

1106
01:23:34,782 --> 01:23:37,752
His demands will never end.

1107
01:23:38,452 --> 01:23:41,547
My needs will be fulfilled
only when his are not fulfilled.

1108
01:23:42,189 --> 01:23:43,247
Give me.

1109
01:23:44,391 --> 01:23:46,155
| will give whatever |
have to give. - Okay.

1110
01:23:46,260 --> 01:23:47,284
In front of a witness.

1111
01:23:47,595 --> 01:23:49,188
Shall I bring a witness?

1112
01:23:49,263 --> 01:23:52,255
No. Your admirers are here.

1113
01:23:52,366 --> 01:23:55,495
Who?
- Come, brothers.

1114
01:23:58,806 --> 01:24:00,205
Disloyal village head.

1115
01:24:00,274 --> 01:24:02,436
You want to ruin us and become rich.

1116
01:24:02,609 --> 01:24:04,407
We spared your life.

1117
01:24:04,478 --> 01:24:06,037
That's why laborers have
to fight amongst themselves.

1118
01:24:06,147 --> 01:24:08,411
You should be hacked to death.
-Yes.

1119
01:24:10,084 --> 01:24:11,381
Stop. Stop. Stop.

1120
01:24:11,485 --> 01:24:13,010
Give my dhoti back.

1121
01:24:13,120 --> 01:24:15,452
Forgive us. He had brainwashed us.

1122
01:24:16,056 --> 01:24:18,320
It's better late than never.
-Yes.

1123
01:24:18,425 --> 01:24:20,484
Come on. Get out.

1124
01:24:20,761 --> 01:24:23,128
The one who is coming?
-Yes.

1125
01:24:40,147 --> 01:24:41,171
God bless you, dear.
- Hello.

1126
01:25:01,568 --> 01:25:03,468
Hello.
- Hello.

1127
01:25:04,138 --> 01:25:05,697
| was waiting for you.

1128
01:25:06,874 --> 01:25:10,071
You?
- | live in Jai Prakash's house.

1129
01:25:10,578 --> 01:25:13,206
Junior master wears..

1130
01:25:13,581 --> 01:25:15,777
He watches it all
the time and drinks.

1131
01:25:16,150 --> 01:25:18,244
| wanted to know why he does that.

1132
01:25:18,352 --> 01:25:23,586
His sister told me you
saved him from death penalty.

1133
01:25:23,891 --> 01:25:25,552
So | wanted to meet you.

1134
01:25:26,293 --> 01:25:29,160
| found out you come
here every Friday.

1135
01:25:29,330 --> 01:25:31,560
So | came to meet you.

1136
01:25:32,233 --> 01:25:34,429
Your name?
- Vidya.

1137
01:25:34,635 --> 01:25:37,570
Junior sir has
helped the village a lot.

1138
01:25:38,138 --> 01:25:39,572
You saved him.

1139
01:25:39,874 --> 01:25:41,467
The entire village
is indebted to you.

1140
01:25:41,675 --> 01:25:43,541
You adore him.

1141
01:25:44,345 --> 01:25:46,177
Why don't you make
him give up drinking?

1142
01:25:47,314 --> 01:25:50,807
Nobody in the village has the
guts to talk in front of him.

1143
01:25:51,719 --> 01:25:55,587
If you explain to him once,
he will give up drinking.

1144
01:25:55,756 --> 01:25:59,283
If that happens, |
will be really pleased.

1145
01:25:59,660 --> 01:26:03,392
Look, sister. God
hears everybody's prayer.

1146
01:26:03,464 --> 01:26:07,492
Pray devoutly. Your
wish will be fulfilled.

1147
01:26:08,402 --> 01:26:09,426
| am leaving.

1148
01:26:14,708 --> 01:26:15,766
Uncle.

1149
01:26:16,444 --> 01:26:18,538
Who is it? Get lost.

1150
01:26:19,246 --> 01:26:20,304
Uncle.
- Get lost.

1151
01:26:24,552 --> 01:26:25,747
Sir, hello.

1152
01:26:25,953 --> 01:26:28,615
Why have such
affluent people come here?

1153
01:26:28,722 --> 01:26:29,848
Uncle, Come here.
-Yes.

1154
01:26:30,558 --> 01:26:32,890
| don't know how you will do it.

1155
01:26:33,260 --> 01:26:36,252
Kidnap Vidya from Suraj's house.
- What are you saying?

1156
01:26:36,363 --> 01:26:37,831
Otherwise it will be difficult
for you to live in this village.

1157
01:26:37,932 --> 01:26:39,195
Don't forget that.

1158
01:26:39,533 --> 01:26:42,195
You can't judge a
person's character by his caste.

1159
01:26:42,503 --> 01:26:43,561
Lotus grows in muddy water.

1160
01:26:43,671 --> 01:26:45,639
We don't throw it away.
We offer it to God.

1161
01:26:45,739 --> 01:26:47,207
What's the meaning of
caste discrimination?

1162
01:26:47,775 --> 01:26:49,402
There is a difference
between words and action.

1163
01:26:49,744 --> 01:26:52,475
Do you know what is
written on our village walls?

1164
01:26:52,579 --> 01:26:53,603
What is written?

1165
01:26:53,814 --> 01:26:55,748
| feel ashamed to tell you.

1166
01:26:55,849 --> 01:26:57,214
You tell him.

1167
01:26:57,485 --> 01:26:59,453
You have kept a girl in your house.

1168
01:26:59,620 --> 01:27:01,611
People have criticized it.

1169
01:27:01,722 --> 01:27:05,556
It's written, "Suraj has kept a
whore in his house as his wife."

1170
01:27:05,659 --> 01:27:06,820
"He gives summons in the village."

1171
01:27:06,927 --> 01:27:08,395
"And he has kept a
whore in his house."

1172
01:27:21,809 --> 01:27:22,867
Brother.

1173
01:28:04,852 --> 01:28:07,412
With God as the witness
| accept her as my wife.

1174
01:29:01,575 --> 01:29:04,670
If you want to wipe the
tears of 'Devdasi' women..

1175
01:29:04,778 --> 01:29:06,746
..who become
victims of wealthy men..

1176
01:29:06,914 --> 01:29:09,349
..marry them and give
them respect in the society.

1177
01:29:09,884 --> 01:29:12,546
Don't sell them as dancers.

1178
01:29:16,991 --> 01:29:18,720
Did you see him marry her?
- Yes, sir.

1179
01:29:18,793 --> 01:29:19,851
Yes, sir.

1180
01:29:20,494 --> 01:29:23,020
| spend money and he marries her.

1181
01:29:23,130 --> 01:29:24,655
If sir asks me, what will | say?

1182
01:29:24,765 --> 01:29:27,063
Say she got married.
- Shut up.

1183
01:30:25,426 --> 01:30:26,484
Ma'am.

1184
01:30:26,594 --> 01:30:28,392
Shall we go?
- After some time.

1185
01:30:35,936 --> 01:30:37,495
| was waiting for you.

1186
01:30:39,140 --> 01:30:40,403
Come with me.

1187
01:30:46,614 --> 01:30:47,638
I--

1188
01:30:48,883 --> 01:30:49,907
Got married?

1189
01:30:50,451 --> 01:30:52,442
| was waiting to congratulate you.

1190
01:30:55,189 --> 01:30:56,554
How was your nuptial night?

1191
01:30:57,157 --> 01:30:59,785
Next year you will have
either a girl or a boy.

1192
01:31:00,761 --> 01:31:02,092
Pray for that.

1193
01:31:07,101 --> 01:31:08,569
Did | say something wrong?

1194
01:31:10,204 --> 01:31:11,467
Don't misunderstand me.

1195
01:31:12,606 --> 01:31:14,870
He didn't marry me
because he loves me.

1196
01:31:15,943 --> 01:31:17,809
He married me
because he took pity on me.

1197
01:31:18,746 --> 01:31:20,771
And to fulfill the
duty of a true man.

1198
01:31:24,251 --> 01:31:27,516
| thought the man who
gives sermons to the world..

1199
01:31:27,621 --> 01:31:28,816
..will be happy because of you.

1200
01:31:29,990 --> 01:31:31,082
His heart..

1201
01:31:34,628 --> 01:31:38,223
Vidya, will you say this on Friday,
standing in the temple?

1202
01:31:39,166 --> 01:31:41,066
Not at all.

1203
01:31:41,802 --> 01:31:43,201
Because of that your life..

1204
01:31:43,504 --> 01:31:44,869
Initially | also
thought the same thing.

1205
01:31:45,706 --> 01:31:49,802
But | don't want to incur the
sin of another life being ruined.

1206
01:31:51,679 --> 01:31:54,740
Next Friday please send him.

1207
01:32:09,930 --> 01:32:13,560
Lord, fulfill everybody's wish.

1208
01:32:24,878 --> 01:32:26,004
Keep this in the car.

1209
01:32:29,950 --> 01:32:32,749
Seeing your black clothes
and beard, | understood.

1210
01:32:34,121 --> 01:32:36,021
Your plight is such because of me.

1211
01:32:37,858 --> 01:32:39,155
| am responsible for this.

1212
01:32:39,627 --> 01:32:41,618
Sita's trial by fire
in the Ashok garden.

1213
01:32:42,730 --> 01:32:43,925
| was wondering what punishment..

1214
01:32:44,031 --> 01:32:45,089
..you will get for meeting me.

1215
01:32:45,666 --> 01:32:46,724
Why only Sita?

1216
01:32:47,234 --> 01:32:51,068
What Mandodari must
have gone through?

1217
01:32:55,009 --> 01:32:56,670
Don't ruin your life for me.

1218
01:32:57,144 --> 01:33:00,603
If you give 1% of the
love that you gave me..

1219
01:33:00,715 --> 01:33:02,683
..to Vidya, who
considers you her life..

1220
01:33:03,250 --> 01:33:04,979
..she will
sacrifice her life for you.

1221
01:33:06,086 --> 01:33:07,952
Calling her your
wife is not enough.

1222
01:33:08,856 --> 01:33:10,290
She needs love as well.

1223
01:33:10,791 --> 01:33:15,251
Look, Veena. I am a man. Not a
corpse that I will forget my past.

1224
01:33:15,929 --> 01:33:17,761
| didn't come here
to give you a lecture.

1225
01:33:18,599 --> 01:33:20,693
| have come to tell you the
difference between lie and truth.

1226
01:33:22,236 --> 01:33:26,605
Vidya had faith that | will
make you give up drinking.

1227
01:33:27,241 --> 01:33:29,767
She came to me
thinking | will persuade you.

1228
01:33:30,077 --> 01:33:31,567
She fulfilled her duty.

1229
01:33:32,113 --> 01:33:35,674
You loved me before you married her.

1230
01:33:36,617 --> 01:33:38,745
You don't know what
endeavors she has done..

1231
01:33:38,853 --> 01:33:40,343
..so that you give up drinking.

1232
01:33:41,222 --> 01:33:43,088
After her marriage |
came to congratulate her.

1233
01:33:44,191 --> 01:33:47,354
She smiled and said,
"He married me."

1234
01:33:48,062 --> 01:33:50,121
"He put the
Mangalsutra around my neck."

1235
01:33:51,966 --> 01:33:56,836
She told me lovingly, "I
have borrowed this Mangalsutra."

1236
01:33:58,205 --> 01:33:59,263
Listen to me.

1237
01:33:59,940 --> 01:34:01,704
A woman wants only love.

1238
01:34:02,143 --> 01:34:05,841
You didn't realize how
much your wife loves you.

1239
01:34:06,780 --> 01:34:07,941
| regret that.

1240
01:34:08,048 --> 01:34:09,914
If possible, listen to me.

1241
01:34:10,351 --> 01:34:12,183
Live with her lovingly.

1242
01:34:13,721 --> 01:34:14,779
This is what | pray for.

1243
01:34:30,271 --> 01:34:31,932
Why did you meet him?

1244
01:34:32,773 --> 01:34:35,367
You would tell me you are
going to the temple to worship.

1245
01:34:35,976 --> 01:34:37,740
You love him so much?

1246
01:34:38,412 --> 01:34:39,971
| swear on you.

1247
01:34:40,247 --> 01:34:42,944
| met him without your
permission for the first time.

1248
01:34:43,217 --> 01:34:44,275
Don't misunderstand me.

1249
01:34:45,386 --> 01:34:46,717
Disloyal woman.

1250
01:35:42,977 --> 01:35:45,105
'You don't know what
endeavors she has done..'

1251
01:35:45,179 --> 01:35:46,874
'..so that you give up drinking.'

1252
01:36:04,265 --> 01:36:05,323
Vidya..

1253
01:36:06,267 --> 01:36:08,167
..I have hurt your feelings.
Forgive me.

1254
01:36:13,240 --> 01:36:16,073
| didn't take pity
on you and marry you.

1255
01:36:30,257 --> 01:36:34,785
"Your melody is on my breaths."

1256
01:36:35,296 --> 01:36:39,961
| got you. What else do | want?"

1257
01:36:40,301 --> 01:36:45,205
"Beloved, you are my worship."

1258
01:36:45,940 --> 01:36:50,969
"Beloved, | have
forgone my anklets."

1259
01:37:06,494 --> 01:37:11,056
"Your melody is on my breaths."

1260
01:37:11,465 --> 01:37:16,096
| got you. What else do | want?"

1261
01:37:16,437 --> 01:37:21,238
"Beloved, you are my worship."

1262
01:37:22,009 --> 01:37:26,503
"Beloved, | have
forgone my anklets."

1263
01:37:27,114 --> 01:37:29,208
“In my breaths."

1264
01:37:29,550 --> 01:37:32,076
“In my arms."

1265
01:37:32,186 --> 01:37:34,814
"In the spring."

1266
01:38:18,566 --> 01:38:23,595
"1 capture the image of
my beloved in my eyes."

1267
01:38:24,004 --> 01:38:29,033
"From my eyes to my heart."

1268
01:38:29,176 --> 01:38:34,114
"1 capture the image of
my beloved in my eyes."

1269
01:38:34,381 --> 01:38:39,285
"From my eyes to my heart."

1270
01:38:39,587 --> 01:38:44,423
"You have loved me."

1271
01:38:44,692 --> 01:38:49,630
"And expressed your love."

1272
01:38:50,097 --> 01:38:54,591
"We shouldn't ever separate."

1273
01:38:55,002 --> 01:38:59,166
"Your melody is on my breaths."

1274
01:38:59,707 --> 01:39:04,372
| got you. What else do | want?"

1275
01:39:04,979 --> 01:39:09,610
"Beloved, you are my worship."

1276
01:39:10,384 --> 01:39:15,515
"Beloved, | have
forgone my anklets."

1277
01:39:52,226 --> 01:39:57,255
"Tell the spring my
beloved is my ornament."

